{
  "texts": [
    "The disruptive potential of LLMs to facilitate both good and malicious deeds have since generated extremes of excitement and apprehension (Bubeck et al. 2023).",
    "History has taught us that humanity will continue to use innovative technology for both good (e.g., curing diseases), and bad (e.g., synthesizing untraceable computer viruses).",
    "This trend is likely to continue as developers march towards achieving artificial general intelligence (AGI {XE \"AGI:artificial general intelligence\"}), then artificial super intelligence (ASI {XE \"ASI:artificial super intelligence\"}), and beyond.",
    "A continued lack of understanding about how developers build LLMs to do what they do currently will further contribute to the fear and suspicion surrounding AI developments.",
    "The goal of this primer is to help demystify how developers build LLMs like Chat-GPT and Bard."
  ]
}